

This project includes a basic Flask blog website for demonstration purposes on how to use Docker.



To run this on your machine follow these steps (without the dockerfile):

1.) Install python https://www.python.org/downloads/
2.) Clone the repo
3.) Install virtualenv using pip (run the below command inside of the volts directory)
  - pip install virtualenv
4.) Create your virtual enviroment
  - python -m venv venv
5.) Activate the virtual enviroment 
  - Windows Command Prompt
    venv\Scripts\activate.bat			
  - Windows PowerShell
    venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
  - Linux & MacOS
    venv/bin/activate
6.) Install project requirements (you must run this command inside the directory in which the requirements file exists)
  - pip install requirements.txt
7.) Now you can either run
  - python run.py 
 or
  Windows
    - set FLASK_APP=run.py
    - flask run
  MacOS & Linux
   - export FLASK_APP=run.py
   - flask run
   
 You should now be able to see the website on localhost
 
      
